title: Arsenal transfer news: Henry Onyekuru battle with Chelsea | Metro News
text:
Arsenal and Chelsea get Henry Onyekuru transfer boost gossip Mark Brus for Metro.co.uk Tuesday 28 Feb 2017 11:47 am Henry Onyekuru is attracting interest from top clubs (Picture: Getty) 
Arsenal and Chelsea can reportedly seal the transfer of highly-rated Nigerian winger Henry Onyekuru this summer as his club are prepared to let him leave for £6million. Rumour Mill: our round-up of football gossip, rumours and speculation 
The 19-year-old is currently on the books at Belgian side Eupen, and has attracted plenty of rumoured interest from top clubs in the last few months. 
Arsenal have been mentioned alongside Chelsea are being among the main contenders for his signature ahead of next season, with Eupen ready to sell, according to the Daily Mail . Onyekuru, 19, looks an exciting young talent (Picture: Getty) 
Sevilla, Borussia Dortmund, Borussia Monchengladbach and Lille are also said to be among the youngster’s admirers, though a move to the Premier League would surely be a tempting offer.
